<paragraph id="8BA49659C271FFBC4FA4FDE48F9C1AE6" blockId="14.[151,672,620,646]" box="[151,672,620,646]" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">
<heading id="D0EC2135C271FFBC4FA4FDE48F9C1AE6" bold="true" box="[151,672,620,646]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="14" pageNumber="567" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C1BEDDAC271FFBC4FA4FDE48F9C1AE6" authority="Williamson, 1919" authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[151,672,620,646]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peregrinum">
<emphasis id="B96F4A4BC271FFBC4FA4FDE48F9C1AE6" bold="true" box="[151,672,620,646]" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis id="B96F4A4BC271FFBC4FA4FDE48CFC1AE6" bold="true" box="[151,448,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">Heteragrion peregrinum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AEBA8C271FFBC4EF4FDE48F9C1AE6" author="Williamson" box="[455,672,620,646]" pageId="14" pageNumber="567" refString="Williamson, E. B. (1919) Results of the University of Michigan-Williamson expedition to Colombia, 1916 - 1917. IV. Notes on the species of the genus Heteragrion Selys with descriptions of new species (Odonata). Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology University of Michigan, 68, 1 - 89." type="journal article" year="1919">Williamson, 1919</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA49659C271FFBC4FA4FD3A8C741BC3" blockId="14.[151,1436,690,931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">
This species, together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BEDDAC271FFBC4EFEFD3A8E561AAB" authority="Calvert, 1931" authorityName="Calvert" authorityYear="1931" box="[461,874,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Platystictidae" genus="Palaemnema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edmondi">
<emphasis id="B96F4A4BC271FFBC4EFEFD3A8FFB1AAB" box="[461,711,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">Palaemnema edmondi</emphasis>
Calvert, 1931
</taxonomicName>
, are the only ones found in the 
<collectingRegion id="49DF58BBC271FFBC4BE3FD3A88701AAB" box="[1232,1356,690,715]" country="Colombia" name="Magdalena" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">Magdalena</collectingRegion>
Valley by the Williamsons in 1917, which have not been seen again since their expedition. The Williamsons collected 
<specimenCount id="9D1D5DD0C271FFBC4AB3FD5E8C301B73" pageId="14" pageNumber="567" type="generic">50 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BEDDAC271FFBC4E05FD748CE11B73" authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[310,477,764,787]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peregrinum">
<emphasis id="B96F4A4BC271FFBC4E05FD748CE11B73" box="[310,477,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">H. peregrinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in just one week, which shows this species used to be a common inhabitant of the 
<collectingRegion id="49DF58BBC271FFBC4FA4FC968C281B57" box="[151,276,798,823]" country="Colombia" name="Magdalena" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">Magdalena</collectingRegion>
Valley streams (
<typeStatus id="54A028FBC271FFBC4EE3FC978F3E1B57" box="[464,514,799,823]" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">type</typeStatus>
locality 
<figureCitation id="13208ADCC271FFBC4D55FC968F9B1B57" box="[614,679,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1999,2021]" captionTargetBox="[163,1421,1085,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1061,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Recorded localities in Colombia for H. aequatoriale, H. erythrogastrum and H. peregrinum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1048661/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The fact that it has not even been registered any more, makes 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BEDDAC271FFBC4AB2FC978C251B3B" authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peregrinum">
<emphasis id="B96F4A4BC271FFBC4AB2FC978C251B3B" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">H. peregrinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a species of special interest, which was recently assessed as Critically Endangered in the 
<collectionCode id="ED0A0E9CC271FFBC4A37FCCB88741B3B" box="[1284,1352,835,859]" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">IUCN</collectionCode>
red list (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AEBA8C271FFBC4FADFCEE8C981B1F" author="Bota-Sierra" box="[158,420,870,895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="567" refString="Bota-Sierra, C. A., Maufray, B., Palacino-Rodriguez, F., Hofmann, J., Tennessen, K., Rache, L. &amp; Tognelli, M. F. (2016) Estado de conservacion de las libelulas de los Andes Tropicales. In: Tognelli, M. F., Lasso, C. A., Bota-Sierra, C. A., Jimenez- Segura, L. F. &amp; Cox, N. A. (Eds.), Estado de Conservacion y Distribucion de la Biodiversidad de Agua Dulce en los Andes Tropicales. UICN Gland, Suiza, Cambridge &amp; Arlington, pp. 67 - 86." type="book chapter" year="2016">
Bota-Sierra 
<emphasis id="B96F4A4BC271FFBC4E1BFCEF8C5D1B1F" box="[296,353,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Here we present the first pictures of this species, from 
<typeStatus id="54A028FBC271FFBC4B2FFCEF89BB1B1F" box="[1052,1159,871,895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">paratypes</typeStatus>
deposited at RWG (
<figureCitation id="13208ADCC271FFBC4A59FCEE8D921BC3" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[255,1307,198,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[236,1341,195,1820]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Face color pattern. H. aequatoriale, males: a, Cordillera Central, Santo Domingo; b, Cordillera Occidental, Jericó; c, Cordillera Occidental, Anchicayá; d, Cordillera Central, Carmen de Viboral; e, Cordillera Occidental, PNN Tatamá; f, Cordillera Central, San Luis; g, Cordillera Central, Amalfí; h, female, Cordillera Occidental, PNN Tatamá. H. calendulum: i, male, Santa Cecilia; j, female, Santa Cecilia; k, male Holotype (UMMZ), La Cristalina. H. peregrinum: l, female Paratype (RWG), La Cristalina. H. m. atroterminatum: m, male, Anchicayá; n, female, Santa Cecilia. H. tatama: o, male, PNN Tatamá; p, female, PNN Tatamá. Picture k, by Dr. O´Brien and l, by Dr. Garrison." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1048665/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">Figs 3l</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13208ADCC271FFBC4F88FC038DC91BC3" box="[187,245,907,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[176,1420,190,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[176,1420,188,1867]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsum of prothorax: a, H. aequatoriale female, PNN Tatamá. H. calendulum Santa Cecilia, b, male; c, female. d, H. m. atroterminatum female, Santa Cecilia. H. tatama PNN Tatamá, e, female; f, male. Female prothoracic intersternite: g, H. aequatoriale, PNN Tatamá; H. calendulum: h, Santa Cecilia; i, Rancho Frío (Panama); j, H. erythrogastrum, La Cristalina; k, H. m. atroterminatum, Santa Cecilia; H. m. mitratum: l, La Cristalina; m, La Fría (Venezuela); n-o, H. peregrinum, female Paratype La Cristalina; p, H. tatama, PNN Tatamá. Pictures l-o by Dr. Garrison." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1048667/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">4n–o</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13208ADCC271FFBC4E32FC028C071BC3" box="[257,315,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[191,1401,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[191,1401,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. a, Heteragrion erythrogastrum, Remedios, habitus male. Heteragrion peregrinum, La Cristalina: b, female Paratype, c, male Paratype. Heteragrion mitratum atroterminatum, Santa Cecilia: d, male cercus in middorsal view; e, male cercus in ventral view. f, H. calendulum, Darien, male cercus in ventral view (Photographs b and c by Dr. Garrison)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1048675/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="567">8b–c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
